<subSubSection id="C31E01A5FF92FFBCC9C0FADEFEE6B274" pageId="7" pageNumber="200" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BBB522EFF92FFBCC9C0FADEFD53B138" blockId="7.[136,1452,1309,1552]" pageId="7" pageNumber="200">
<emphasis id="B9708E3CFF92FFBCC9C0FADEFE6FB153" bold="true" box="[136,465,1309,1336]" pageId="7" pageNumber="200">Distribution and habitat:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C0429ADFF92FFBCC89AFADDFD39B15C" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[466,647,1310,1336]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="200" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirta">
<emphasis id="B9708E3CFF92FFBCC89AFADDFD39B15C" box="[466,647,1310,1336]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="200">Euphorbia hirta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a worldwide tropical and subtropical weed. In the state of 
<collectingRegion id="49C09CCCFF92FFBCCC72FADDFA12B15C" box="[1338,1452,1310,1336]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="7" pageNumber="200">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
the species is very common, mainly in disturbed areas.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBB522EFF92FFBCC9F5FAA6FA22B1E4" blockId="7.[136,1452,1309,1552]" box="[189,1436,1381,1408]" pageId="7" pageNumber="200">
