<paragraph id="8BBB522EFF92FFBCC9F5FA4AFEE6B274" blockId="7.[136,1452,1309,1552]" pageId="7" pageNumber="200">
<emphasis id="B9708E3CFF92FFBCC9F5FA4AFE11B1C0" bold="true" box="[189,431,1417,1444]" pageId="7" pageNumber="200">Taxonomic notes:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C0429ADFF92FFBCC8E6FA49FDD9B1C0" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[430,615,1418,1444]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="200" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirta">
<emphasis id="B9708E3CFF92FFBCC8E6FA49FDD9B1C0" box="[430,615,1418,1444]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="200">Euphorbia hirta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0429ADFF92FFBCCA0AFA48FC4FB1C0" authorityName="Persoon" authorityYear="1806" box="[834,1009,1418,1444]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="200" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ophthalmica">
<emphasis id="B9708E3CFF92FFBCCA0AFA48FC4FB1C0" box="[834,1009,1418,1444]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="200">E. ophthalmica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs from it in having capitate dichasia along all the stem while, while 
<taxonomicName id="4C0429ADFF92FFBCCB2DFA6CFCAAB1AC" authorityName="Persoon" authorityYear="1806" box="[613,788,1454,1480]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="200" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ophthalmica">
<emphasis id="B9708E3CFF92FFBCCB2DFA6CFCAAB1AC" box="[613,788,1454,1480]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="200">E. ophthalmica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
these are restricted to the terminal portion of the stems. Besides, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0429ADFF92FFBCC9A4FA10FEFEB188" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[236,320,1490,1516]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="200" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirta">
<emphasis id="B9708E3CFF92FFBCC9A4FA10FEFEB188" box="[236,320,1490,1516]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="200">E. hirta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is an erect herb, with stems branched only near the base, and its leaves are generally bigger than those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0429ADFF92FFBCC9EEFA34FEEFB274" authorityName="Persoon" authorityYear="1806" box="[166,337,1526,1552]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="200" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ophthalmica">
<emphasis id="B9708E3CFF92FFBCC9EEFA34FEEFB274" box="[166,337,1526,1552]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="200">E. ophthalmica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
